## My process

### Built with

- Semantic HTML5 markup
- Flexbox
- CSS Grid

### What I learned

I found that CSS Grid is the best way to style the content of cards as seen in this project.

```css
.card {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-rows: 200px 150px 100px 150px;
  grid-template-columns: 350px;
  grid-template-areas: "image" "description" "plan" "checkout";

  position: absolute;
  top: 50%;
  left: 50%;
  transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
  background-color: white;
  border-radius: 20px;
  box-shadow: 4px 6px 7px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
  overflow: hidden;
}
```

### Useful resources

- [Box Shadows](https://getcssscan.com/css-box-shadow-examples) - This helped me to find a nice box shadow for my card reason.

